{
  "texts": [
    "Pooling layers reduce the spatial dimensions of the data, enhancing computational efficiency and helping to prevent overfitting.",
    "The flattened output, a 1D vector, is processed by fully connected layers for classification.",
    "Figure 4 illustrates this structure for fossil classification from RGB images.",
    "Despite CNNs offering significant accuracy improvements, they require extensive data and computational resources, particularly for 3D images, and can suffer from overfitting.",
    "Regularization and data augmentation are used to address these challenges, especially in fossil image analysis."
  ]
}